<topic id="wa-integrate-ai-positron-enterprise">
  <title>Integrating Web Author with AI Positron Enterprise</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>AI Positron Enterprise</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_mjr_dgk_54b">The <ph keyref="webappProduct"/> includes a plugin that provides the
      ability to integrate Web Author with a specific AI engine (<b>OpenAI</b>, <b>Microsoft Azure
        OpenAI</b> or <b>Anthropic Claude</b>). The connection details to the AI engine can be
      configured by following the steps below.</p>
    <section id="installing_the_plugin">
      <title>Configuring the Web Author AI Positron Plugin</title>
      <ol id="ol_njr_dgk_54b">
        <li id="li_ojr_dgk_54b">Go to your <xref href="webapp-admin-page.dita#webapp-admin-page">Administration
            Page</xref>.</li>
        <li id="li_pjr_dgk_54b">Select <uicontrol>Plugins</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li id="li_qjr_dgk_54b">
          <p id="p_rjr_dgk_54b">Click the <uicontrol><image href="../img/ConfigureSearchScope16.png"
                id="image_rbz_csl_3jb"/>Configure</uicontrol> icon next to the <b>Web Author AI
              Positron</b> plugin to open the <uicontrol>Plugin configuration</uicontrol> dialog
            box.</p>
        </li>
        <li id="step-4">
          <p>Configure the connector and for the specific connector configure the necessary
            details.</p>
          <p>
            <dl id="dl_o1f_3sk_21c">
              <dlentry>
                <dt>AI Connector</dt>
                <dd>Specifies the connector type: <b>OpenAI</b>, <b>Microsoft Azure OpenAI</b> or
                    <b>Anthropic Claude</b>.</dd>
              </dlentry>
            </dl>
          </p>
          <p id="p_kyd_hym_21c"><u><b>OpenAI:</b></u></p>
          <p>If <b>OpenAI</b> is chosen as the connector type, the following settings are
              available:<dl conkeyref="reusables-ai-plugin/openai-settings" id="dl_ixy_ncb_y1c">
              <dlentry>
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
            </dl></p>
          <p id="p_rvw_jym_21c"><u><b>Microsoft Azure OpenAI:</b></u></p>
          <p>If <b>Microsoft Azure OpenAI</b> is chosen as the connector type, the following
            settings are available:<dl
              conkeyref="reusables-ai-plugin/reusables-ms-azure-ai-settings" id="dl_eqr_4cb_y1c">
              <dlentry>
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
            </dl></p>
          <p id="claude"><u><b>Anthropic Claude:</b></u></p>
          <p>If <b>Anthropic Claude</b> is chosen as the connector type, the following settings are
              available:<dl conkeyref="reusables-ai-plugin/reusables-claude-settings"
              id="dl_ggk_pcb_y1c">
              <dlentry>
                <dt/>
                <dd/>
              </dlentry>
            </dl></p>
          <note id="note_lkp_hlq_g1c">You can use <xref href="editor-variables.dita">editor
              variables</xref> such as <codeph>${env(ENV_NAME)}</codeph> in all configuration and
            header parameter values.</note>
        </li>
        <li id="li_tjr_dgk_54b">Click <uicontrol>Apply</uicontrol>.</li>
        <li id="li_ujr_dgk_54b"><xref href="webauthor-restart.dita">Restart <ph keyref="webappProduct"/></xref>.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>
